Sorry if this has been answered elsewhere.  I can't seem to find an elegant solution.

Suppose I have a `clone` method on some controller (`Router`):

```js
controller.post(':id/clone', function (req, res, next) {
  // simulate the GET request to retrieve the resource as the user normally would see it
  // maybe change a couple of values
  // simulate the POST request to create the clone and return the response as usual
});
```

This internal simulation is necessary because I have a handful of decorators attached to requests that filter and validate certain properties based on user permissions, etc., and it would be a pain to refactor them into this `clone` decorator, especially if I can simulate the requests.

I've done something like this before, but it was pretty hacked together, as I had to dig into the internals of Express and "fake" the request and response handler. Surely there's a better way?

